element.name: Dodder - Dropping Well by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

long-description.p: One of a series of caches along the Dodder River – the paths linking these caches are wheelchair and buggy/pram passable, unless otherwise stated. All the caches in this series are also accessible to the wheelchair user, unless otherwise stated.

This one is a micro-cache, hidden in a small park next to the car-park at N53 18.476 W 006 15.338 and is accessible by, and from, wheelchair. You might take the time to have a look in the river at the back of the pub – there are a couple of wildlife sculptures to be seen! Given the Dublin custom of naming statues/monuments somewhat irreverently, this one escaped lightly, being christened Ryan O’Neal!!
This cache can easily be done in conjunction with “Dodder – Dartry Park” and “Dodder – St Annes”

element.encoded-hints: Sit down and enjoy the view!

As we rounded the corner it was easy to spot the obvious place to hide this one. Thankfully it was raining (for a change) an so the muggles were all tucked up inside and ignoring us. Found with CMB50. TNLNSL and then went into the pub to watch the All Ireland GAA final... great match!
